the 2-60 range. Holographic characteristics were also obtained 
for this material. The relationships of the initial, final and 
corrected diffraction efficiency as a function of the initial 
time of exposure for the 632.8 nm wavelength are also provided. 
The gain corresponding to the diffraction efficiency curves is 
also shown in the graphs. The mechanism of optical amplification 
in the photopolymer material is discussed. Figures 6, references 
